 <html:p>By <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-002C.xml" title="from quasi-inverses to coherent inverses" addr="forest://erct/erct-002C" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-002C" /></fr:link>, it suffices to find a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000X.xml" title="quasi-inverse" addr="forest://erct/erct-000X" type="local">quasi-inverse</fr:link> to the composite <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\circ  f]]></fr:tex>; we take this to be the composite (<fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-002L.xml" title="composition of quasi-invertible maps" addr="forest://erct/erct-002L" type="local">Construction <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-002L" /></fr:link>) of the underlying <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000X.xml" title="quasi-inverse" addr="forest://erct/erct-000X" type="local">quasi-inverses</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter>
