            <fr:title text="composition of quasi-invertible maps">composition of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000X.xml" title="quasi-inverse" addr="forest://erct/erct-000X" type="local">quasi-invertible</fr:link> maps</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Construction</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002L.agda" type="external">erct-002L.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  B\to  C]]></fr:tex> be <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000X.xml" title="quasi-inverse" addr="forest://erct/erct-000X" type="local">quasi-invertible</fr:link> maps. Then the composite <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\circ  f\colon  A \to  C]]></fr:tex> is quasi-invertible, with sectionhood and retractionhood witnesses given by those of the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-002I.xml" title="composition of sections" addr="forest://erct/erct-002I" type="local">composites of the component sections</fr:link> and <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-002J.xml" title="composition of retractions" addr="forest://erct/erct-002J" type="local">retractions</fr:link>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
              <fr:month>12</fr:month>
              <fr:day>30</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:addr>forest://erct/erct-002C</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-002C.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="from quasi-inverses to coherent inverses">from <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000X.xml" title="quasi-inverse" addr="forest://erct/erct-000X" type="local">quasi-inverses</fr:link> to coherent <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000W.xml" title="inverse" addr="forest://erct/erct-000W" type="local">inverses</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002C.agda" type="external">erct-002C.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f \colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex> have a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000X.xml" title="quasi-inverse" addr="forest://erct/erct-000X" type="local">quasi-inverse</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  B\to  A]]></fr:tex> with incoherent counit <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon \colon  f\circ  g\sim  1_{B}]]></fr:tex> and unit <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\eta \colon  g\circ  f\sim  1_{A}]]></fr:tex>. We can <html:em>correct</html:em> the counit to obtain a coherent <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000W.xml" title="inverse" addr="forest://erct/erct-000W" type="local">inverse</fr:link> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>30</fr:day></fr:date><fr:addr>forest://erct/erct-002C/0</fr:addr><fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-002C/0.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="from quasi-inverses to coherent inverses › forest://erct/erct-002C/0"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-002C.xml" title="from quasi-inverses to coherent inverses" addr="forest://erct/erct-002C" type="local">from <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000X.xml" title="quasi-inverse" addr="forest://erct/erct-000X" type="local">quasi-inverses</fr:link> to coherent <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000W.xml" title="inverse" addr="forest://erct/erct-000W" type="local">inverses</fr:link></fr:link> › forest://erct/erct-002C/0</fr:title><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>The corrected counit <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon ' \colon  g\circ  f\sim  1_{A}]]></fr:tex> is defined like so:</html:p>
 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \epsilon ' x :\equiv 
  \epsilon 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f^{-1} x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}
^{-1} \cdot  \mathsf {act}_{f}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \eta 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen f^{-1} x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 \cdot  \epsilon  x
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <html:p>The coherence <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi \colon  \mathsf {act}_{f}\circ  \eta  \sim  \epsilon '\circ  f]]></fr:tex> can be constructed using our two naturality lemmas <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001V.xml" title="naturality of homotopies" addr="forest://erct/erct-001V" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-001V" /></fr:link> and <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001W.xml" title="naturality of homotopies onto the identity" addr="forest://erct/erct-001W" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-001W" /></fr:link>.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
